news.title: Nobel laureate Ales Beliatski sentenced to 10 years in prison by Belarusian court
news.description: Belarusian Nobel Peace Prize laureate Ales Beliatski was sentenced by a court in Minsk on Friday to 10 years in a maximum-security penal colony, Russia state news agency TASS reports. He was found guilty on the charge of smuggling, according to TASS.

news.title: See the moment verdict was read in Murdaugh trial
news.description: The jury in the double murder trial of Alex Murdaugh has found him guilty of murdering his wife and son. The 54-year-old scion of a prominent and powerful family of local lawyers and solicitors, was also found guilty of two counts of possession of a weapon during the commission of a violent crime in the killings of Margaret "Maggie" Murdaugh and Paul Murdaugh on June 7, 2021.

news.title: Growing alarm in Iran after report that schoolgirls were poisoned
news.description: Reports reveal that in recent months, nearly 900 schoolgirls may have been poisoned across Iran. Some were hospitalized, and others are still experiencing symptoms. CNN's Nima Elbagir reports.

news.title: Adani shares soar as US investor steps in

news.title: Expert: North Korea food crisis at its worst point in decades
news.description: Alarm bells are ringing regarding North Korea's food situation as Kim Jong Un convened a meeting to transform the country's farming capabilities this week.  South Korean officials believe there have been deaths due to starvation and experts point to an ever-worsening situation. Paula Hancocks reports.

news.title: US slams Cambodian opposition figure's 'treason' sentence
news.description: A top Cambodian opposition figure was sentenced to 27 years of house arrest on Friday after being convicted of treason in a verdict the United States denounced as a "miscarriage of justice."

The look — curated by celebrity stylist Julie Ragolia — was topped off by a pair of oversized, 70s tortoise shell eyeglasses.
